BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-5591DFE6-4A21-4760-B9E2-14C316DC26C1
DTSTART:20260302T090000
DTEND:20260302T110000
SUMMARY:Giovanni Gomez [@gxg]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-02 Mon 09:00-11:00>\n1. ☑ discussed (long): REUs\, int
 ernships\, 4+1 masters and PhD options.\n2. ☐ based on best mixing method\
 , repeat with polyelectrolytes (with\n   salt\, see Chen2021b).\n3. ☐ chec
 k PEC consistency/reproducibility by using several samples\n   with 40wt% 
 reline\,\n   1. ☐ set up a time-lapse video to see how much mixing time is
 \n      needed.\n   2. decided that making "fresh" PEC is probably best fo
 r\n      dissolution studies.\n4. ☐ Giovanni needs to read about NMR for P
 EC dissolution before\n   contacting Weiguo.
CATEGORIES:@gxg,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-173108C0-2B26-41A8-8BA7-E431078B0F4F
DTSTART:20260302T120000
DTEND:20260302T130000
SUMMARY:Raina Haq [@rxh]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-02 Mon 12:00-13:00>\n1. ☒ analysis of restriction enzy
 mes re: dam\, dcm\, CpG\, buffers.\n   1. compatible buffers seem possible
 .\n2. ☒ analyze gel of HCR test with newest monomers.\n   1. need extra SD
  card readers.\n3. ☒ analyze gel by Tapiwa past Friday to determine if pla
 smid\n   isolation was successful.\n   1. what are the extra bands and how
  to avoid them?
CATEGORIES:@rxh,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-2C06D84A-E1D8-43E6-BF75-612B254BE5B9
DTSTART:20260303T143000
DTEND:20260303T160000
SUMMARY:Eric Spinney [@exs]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-03 Tue 14:30-16:00>\n• ☑ continue DLS on aqueous gelat
 inized starch but now with amylase.\n  Preheat all samples.\n  • remember 
 that strictly we need RI and viscosity at each\n    temperature.\n• ☐ need
  repeat of 40% and 50% DES\, possibly with both Nanodrop *and*\n  Shimadzu
  instrument.\n  • note that Shimadzu can do averaging (smoothing?) and kin
 etics.
CATEGORIES:@exs,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:SC-E6DB7301-34C9-4CE1-A1FF-8B53590A4D14
DTSTART:20260303T160000
DTEND:20260303T173000
SUMMARY:S: Tapiwa Gono [@mtg @tgp]
DESCRIPTION:1. Recruiting wknd\n   1. Poster sessions\n2. Literature\n   1.
  ☐ Nakano2007b\n3. Plasmid isolation: close to successful\n   1. which mov
 es faster through a gel\; circular or linear?\n   2. /Should we single-cut
  and re-run?/\n4. Engineering self-study\n   1. Share "notes" from 604.\n 
   2. Give homework/practice problems/exam questions from 604.\n5. IDP
CATEGORIES:@mtg,@tgp,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-6AB6EF50-053E-437F-9755-B5F196684920
DTSTART:20260304T114500
DTEND:20260304T140000
SUMMARY:Raina Haq [@rxh]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-04 Wed 11:45-14:00>
CATEGORIES:@rxh,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-B0C0EED1-4D0A-4350-AA61-24EFB9BE2372
DTSTART:20260304T141500
DTEND:20260304T173000
SUMMARY:Giovanni Gomez [@gxg]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-04 Wed 14:15-17:30>\n1. ☑ based on best mixing method\
 , repeat with polyelectrolytes (with\n   2.5M NaCl\, Chen2021b).\n   • do 
 we need a rinse of the PEC with 1.0M NaCl before dissolution\n     tests?
CATEGORIES:@gxg,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-FB94A42F-19D5-4670-A9DF-DCAAB24E182C
DTSTART:20260304T143000
DTEND:20260304T173000
SUMMARY:Eric Spinney [@exs]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-04 Wed 14:30-17:30>\n• ☑ repeat DLS on aqueous gelatin
 ized starch but now with amylase.\n  Preheat all samples.\n  • tested diff
 erent combinations of run numbers and run times.\n    Seems like 6 runs of
  30 seconds (3 min total) is a good\n    compromise.\n  • remember that st
 rictly we need RI and viscosity at each\n    temperature.\n  • to get data
  out of Zetasizer software\, do *not* export\, instead\n    use Edit\,Copy
  and paste in Excel.\n  • note that new ZetaSizer software is backwards-co
 mpatible.
CATEGORIES:@exs,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-20B3BE6C-B00D-4913-9F42-36A78934402A
DTSTART:20260305T140000
DTEND:20260305T170000
SUMMARY:Raina Haq [@rxh]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-05 Thu 14:00-17:00>\n1. ☑ analysis of restriction enzy
 mes re: dam\, dcm\, CpG\, buffers.\n   1. compatible buffers seem possible
 .\n2. ☑ analyze gel of HCR test with newest monomers.\n3. ☑ analyze gel by
  Tapiwa past Friday to determine if plasmid\n   isolation was successful.\
 n   1. what are the extra bands and how to avoid them?
CATEGORIES:@rxh,BRG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T203923Z
UID:TS1-51B524B7-D04B-4E42-9646-15ADAB5C6DA5
DTSTART:20260305T150000
DTEND:20260305T173000
SUMMARY:Giovanni Gomez [@gxg]
DESCRIPTION:<2026-03-05 Thu 15:00-17:30>\n1. ☐ check PEC consistency/reprod
 ucibility by using several samples\n   with 40wt% reline\,\n   1. do we ne
 ed a rinse of the PEC with 1.0M NaCl before\n      dissolution tests?\n   
 2. ☐ set up a time-lapse video to see how much mixing time is\n      neede
 d.\n   3. decided that making "fresh" PEC is probably best for\n      diss
 olution studies.\n2. ☐ Giovanni needs to read about NMR for PEC dissolutio
 n before\n   contacting Weiguo.
CATEGORIES:@gxg,BRG
END:VEVENT
